  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Samuel Joseph May presumably wrote this letter to Caroline Weston. May doesn&apos;t feel as enthusiastic about Florence as he did about Rome. He mentions a ride he took with Caroline Weston in Rome. He tells about his journey from Rome to Florence. &quot;At Arezzo we received tidings of the Revolution in Tuscany,&quot; which May briefly describes. May has been gratified to read the &quot;testimonials to the excellence of Miss Remond&apos;s lectures.&quot; He was very sorry &quot;to learn that the Personal Liberty Bill has failed in the New York and the Massachusetts Legislatures.&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
